<body>
What's the reasoning behind having the content model for &lt;sect&gt; and
friends such that you can only have EITHER a &lt;routinelist&gt; OR other
text in the section?

One might commonly want to write a little bit of introductory text:

  &lt;sect&gt;&lt;title&gt;Descriptions of routines
  &lt;p&gt;Here is a list of the routines used to do such-and-such:
  &lt;routinelist&gt;&lt;codecollection ...&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;You might also want to look at ...
  &lt;/sect&gt;

If you just need to put text before the codecollection, which is 
probably usually the case, then you can do it within the routinelist 
element itself.  However, I can't think of any good semantic 
reason why a section should be barred from containing text content
as well as a routinelist (there may be a technical reason I don't
know of).

