A CONREF attribute on an element is the name of an entity, the contents
of which are taken to be the content of the element, at the parse
stage, I theeeenk, so that the application doesn't have to do anything
else.  This wouldn't really have helped, since CONREF is one of those
potentially useful features which is omitted from XML (I'm pretty
sure).

