Peter Draper mailed me to ask how to include a number of inline
figures (a list of icons plus explanations, I think).  It turns out
that this is not supported, since the &lt;figure&gt; element is implicitly
intended for _floating_ figures.

There's therefore a need for either an analogue of the HTML &lt;img&gt;
element, or perhaps an `inline' attribute to &lt;figure&gt;, and perhaps some
review of the place of figure in the element hierarchy.

